  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>then top, tail, peel and finely dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened and starting to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669722168417-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669722168417-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669722168417-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669722168417-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669722168417-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) as thinly as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced sweet potato[es]</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 2-3 min or until just cooked (this is known as 'parboiling')</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> sliced potato[es]</strong> and leave them to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669722171636-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669722171636-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669722171636-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669722171636-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669722171636-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Strip your<strong> thyme leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop them finely, discard the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669722175794-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669722175794-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669722175794-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669722175794-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669722175794-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lamb has started to brown, stir in 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Stir in your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>,<strong> onion marmalade</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> chopped thyme </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Cook for 1 min and stir it all together to combine</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
